Rating: 3
A great basic soup to springboard into something with bigger flavor. I salt & peppered the chicken in a roasting pan, added 1/2 onion (quartered), a celery stalk (large pieces) & a few cloves of garlic than flash roasted the chicken at 450 degrees for five minutes each side until browned. Transferred chicken & veggies to my pressure cooker, deglazed the roasting pan with chicken stock (or wine) & put with chicken. Pressured the chicken for 10 minutes at 5lbs. Removed chicken & discarded veggies. It is a few more steps but same amount of time and the big flavor is so worth it.

