Rating: 3
I've made this soup a dozen times experimenting with spices (I like tarragon the best), and never really looking at the measurements. I don't like cooking the chicken with skin in the broth beforehand - I did that for the first time tonite. It just adds extra fat that's a pain to remove, and doesn't really enhance the flavor. I like sauteeing the vegetables, adding white wine, and then the broth, then adding raw chopped chicken with no skin or fat. I think that gives the broth a milky look too, and I like that. And I love the lemon-mushrooms added with the noodles. They really make a difference. I don't bother with garlic in the soup, but I think the garlic bread idea sounds grrreat.

