I really really enjoyed this soup. It was an unusually chilly day and was craving chicken noodle soup but didn't want to go through the usual hassle and this was the perfect solution. I'm used to making my own stock, boiling the whole chicken and making my own egg noodles, which results in an all-day affair. With a minimal sacrifice of flavor, this was very very quick, easy, and good. I used a diluted demi-glace for the broth and boneless,skinless breasts which cooked quick and were easy to shred. My family doesn't like mushrooms so I just added some more of the other vegetables which worked very well. I really liked the lemon juice which I have not seen in other recipes, but it added an interesting gourmet-style taste. Very good

