The soup was great and my only question regarding the recipe was the use of 16 cups of canned chicken broth. I'm sure my grandma, if she was alive today, would find it amusing to make chicken soup from scratch with store bought broth instead of water, more seasonings and vegetables. The recipe was very good, but I will keep searching and experimenting until I come up with a satisfactory "old-fashioned chicken soup" that uses no processed products. Maybe I'm getting too old fashioned?

Rating: 4
This is really a great soup. I have made it many times in the past 3 weeks. I also used the cooked rotisserie chicken and skinned and deboned. I actually put the bones in with the broth and simmered for a while. I don't know if this helped at all but the end result was great. I would use the lower sodium 32oz "boxed" broth because it was fairly salty even without the additional salt added. I prefer this soup without the garlic. Follow the easy directions and this is a foolproof soup.

